I've asked a couple times in IRC, and no one can tell why this code gives this error. Makes me think either: 1) it shouldn't be an error, or 2) the error message is wrong, and needs to state the actual error.

``` rust
impl<'a> Decoder<'a> {
    pub fn new(src: &'a str) -> Decoder<'a> {
        // ...
    }
}

/// Decodes a json value from an `io::Reader`
pub fn from_bytes<'a, T:Decodable<Decoder<'a>, Error>>(r: &mut io::Reader) -> DecodeResult<T> {
    match r.read_to_end() {
        Err(e) => Err(IoError(e)),
        Ok(v) => match str::from_utf8(v.as_slice()) {
            None => return Err(ParseError("contents not utf-8".to_owned(), 0, 0)),
            Some(s) => from_str(s)
        }
    }
}

/// Decodes a json value from a string
pub fn from_str<'a, T:Decodable<Decoder<'a>, Error>>(s: &'a str) -> DecodeResult<T> {
    let mut decoder = Decoder::new(s);
    Decodable::decode(&mut decoder)
}
```

Outputs the following error:

